  {
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Ok, some more information: we can avoid this segfault by calling `device.RemoveAllPeers()` before closing.  This waits on the peers being stopped, and avoids the race that leads to segfault.\r\n\r\nThis should fixup the devtunnel, but the bug is still lurking in `wireguard-go` which is a tailscale dependency.  Depending on their usage we could still be subject to these segfaults.  I'll chase the wireguard maintainers about accepting a fix, or fixing it themselves.  It's all via email, so no GitHub issue to track.",
